reviews.text: There is little to no parking. Ticket machine out of order for many different reasons nearly constantly.  Most recently somebody to a fire inside the ticket box. Overall not a great area station has a Little facilities and limited wheelchair access. Location however it’s good for the local school and anybody wishing to commute easily to Leeds or Bradford Foster Square who lives or works around the area. On a week day is incredibly crowded between the hours of four and five.  Students there are polite and well mannered. Shea number of them makes it difficult to compute. Overall station could do however with some upkeep.

This is a commuter station that also provides transport for local schools. Its biggest problem is the severe lack of parking, and trains to and from Leeds are not as frequent as they should be (especially during the morning rush hour or in the early evening).
Nothing here, just two platforms and shelters. Limited parking. Good train connections to Leeds and Bradford.
